This paper deals with the signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) coverage probability in uplink non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) networks. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves mathematical modeling and analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.MM) and Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
